hivis.data

Interface DataMap<K,V>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Data
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    DataTable, GroupedTable<K>, TableView
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDataMap, AbstractDataTable, AbstractMapView, AbstractTableView, AbstractUnmodifiableDataMap, AbstractUnmodifiableDataTable, CalcMap, DataMapDefault, DataTableDefault, DefaultGroupedTable, GroupedSeries, SortedTable, TableViewAppend, TableViewFilterRows, TableViewFunction, TableViewSeries, TableViewSeriesBase, TableViewTranspose

    public interface DataMap<K,V>
extends Data
    Represents a mapping from keys to items. This is a minimal Data structure primarily used to support the series and table grouping functions. Perhaps in the future this will include nice things like filtering and reducing functionality.
    Author:
    O. J. Coleman

      • keys

        DataSeries<K> keys()
        Get a view of the keys in this map. The keys will have the same order as the values provided by values(). Changes to this map will be reflected in the returned series.

      • values

        Get a view of the values in this map. The values will have the same order as the keys provided by keys(). Changes to this map will be reflected in the returned series.
